OL,3,CHow Starmer may have seen off a coup
OL,5,FWould any fury and desire for
OL,6,Fvengeance against the PM be sustained
OL,7,Ffor more than four days, when MPs will
OL,8,Fbe in their constituencies, rather
OL,9,Fthan plotting and winding themselves
OL,10,Fup in the corridors of Westminster?
OL,12,FAnd would any wannabe prime minister
OL,13,Frisk looking treacherous, just as
OL,14,FStarmer has received the imprimatur of
OL,15,Fthe monarch for putative national
OL,16,Frenewal?
OL,18,F"I honestly can't see any route to
OL,19,Freplacing Keir," said one MP who would
OL,20,Flike to see him go.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/3
